“approved  scheme”  means  the  Employees  Provident  Fund  or  any 
pension  or  provident  fund,  scheme  or  society  approved  by  the  
Director General under any written law relating to income tax;

“basis  period”,  in  relation  to  a  chargeable  person  and  a  year  of 
assessment,  means  such  basis  period,  if  any,  as  is  ascertained  in 
accordance with section 5;

“chargeable  petroleum”,  in  relation  to  a  chargeable  person,  means 
petroleum  won  or  obtained  by  that  chargeable  person  from  his 
petroleum operations;

“company”  means  a  body  corporate  and  includes  any  body  of 
persons established with a separate legal identity by or under the laws 
of a place outside Malaysia;

“Inland  Revenue  Board  of  Malaysia”  means  the  Inland  Revenue 
Board  of  Malaysia  established  under  the  Inland  Revenue  Board  of 
Malaysia Act 1995 [Act 533];

“market value”, in relation to any thing, means the price which that 
thing would fetch if sold in a transaction between independent persons 
dealing at arm’s length;

Petroliam Nasional Berhad or the Malaysia-Thailand Joint Authority 
and any other person whereby the parties thereto share any petroleum 
production or any profit derived therefrom;

“prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under section 83 or, in 
relation to a form other than the form mentioned in subsection 71(1), 
prescribed under section 82;

(a)  first, the basis period for his petroleum operations for that 
year shall be ascertained in accordance with Chapter 1 of 
Part III;

(c)  next,  his  adjusted  income  or  adjusted  loss  for  the  basis 
period for that year shall be ascertained in accordance with 
Chapter 3 of that Part;

approval of the Director General or on the date when that 
chargeable  person  ceases  to  be  engaged  in  petroleum 
operations;

(a)  the disposer of the asset is a company and the acquirer of 
the  asset  is  a  partnership  in  which  the  disposer  is  also  a 
partner;

(b)  the disposer of the asset and the acquirer of the asset are the 
same  partnership  but  operating  under  separate  petroleum 
agreements;

(a)  if at  the end of the relevant  period the debt  is  reasonably 
estimated in all the circumstances of the case to be wholly 
irrecoverable, an amount equal to the amount of the debt;

(a)  any disbursements or expenses not being money wholly and 
exclusively  laid  out  or  expended  for  the  purpose  of 
producing the gross income;

(c)  any  amount  in  respect  of  any  payment  to  any  pension, 
provident,  savings,  widows  and  orphans  or  other  similar 
fund or society which is not an approved scheme;

(a)  specify  the  amount  or  additional  amount  of  chargeable 
income and the amount of tax or additional tax payable on 
that chargeable income;

(a)  the inspection of them, the copying of them or the making 
of  extracts  from  them  cannot  reasonably  be  undertaken 
without taking possession of them;

(a)  in the case of a notice served under subsection (2), the year 
of assessment and the amount or additional amount of the 
chargeable income, and the chargeable tax;

penalty is abated or remitted under section 63, so much, if 
any, of the penalty which has not been abated or remitted); 
and

(a)  no  valid  notice  of  appeal  against  an  assessment  has  been 
given  under  section  43  within  the  time  specified  by  that 
section (or any extension thereof);

(c)  the first instalment may be made from the second month of 
the  basis  period  for  that  year  of  assessment  of  that 
chargeable person;

(a)  no  estimate  is  furnished  by  a  chargeable  person,  and  no 
direction is given by the Director General to make payment 
by instalment under subsection (8);

(c)  gives  a  false  answer  (orally  or  in  writing)  to  a  question 
asked  or  request  for  information  made  in  pursuance  of  
this Act;

(d)  prepares  or  maintains  or  authorizes  the  preparation  
or  maintenance  of  false  books  of  account  or  other  
false records;

(a)  obstructs  or  refuses  to  permit  the  entry  of  the  Director 
General or an authorized officer into any land, building or 
place in pursuance of section 33;

(a)  the  order  shall  be  made  in  writing  under  the  hand  of  the 
Director General and there shall be attached to it the written 
admission and request referred to in subsection (1);

(a)  shall consider whether the granting of relief would result in 
the exclusion from charge to tax of income of the applicant; 
and

(a)  altering the incidence of tax which is payable or suffered by 
or which would otherwise have been payable or suffered by 
any chargeable person;

(b)  relieving  any  chargeable  person  from  any  liability  which 
has arisen or which would otherwise have arisen to pay tax 
or to make a return;

(a)  in  the  case  of  a  company,  a  partnership  or  other  body  of 
persons  having  a  registered  office  in  Malaysia,  to  that 
registered office;

the  company,  or 
partnership or other body (wherever that office may 
be situated);

“exploration  asset”  means  an  asset  on  or  for  which  the  chargeable  person  has 
incurred  qualifying  expenditure  in  connection  with  or  in  preparation  for  the 
petroleum operations;

“recovered  expenditure”  means  any  amount  ascertained  in  accordance  with 
paragraphs 7 to 13 to be recovered expenditure in relation to the petroleum operations 
of a chargeable person;

(a)  expenditure incurred by him on the alteration of an existing building for 
the  purpose  of  installing  that  machinery  or  plant  and  other  expenditure 
incurred incidentally to the installation thereof;

(c)  where  that  interest  is  a  leasehold  interest,  the  determination  of  that 
relevant interest otherwise than on the person entitled thereto acquiring 
the reversion;

(c)  the  petroleum  operations  are  carried  on  partly  in  Malaysia  and  partly 
elsewhere,  and  the  asset  is  not  used  wholly  for  the  purposes  of  the 
petroleum operations carried on in Malaysia;

(a)  the Director General may be represented by an authorized officer, a legal 
officer, an advocate either alone or by one of them together with the other 
or others of them;

